-- Eczacibasi to Invest 140 Million Euros in Wind Power, Dunya Says
-- B y   E d i t o r :   [ b n : P R S N = 5 0 0 3 2 7 2 ]   B e n   H o l l a n d   [ ] .
-- 2012-04-12T07:53:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/eczacibasi-to-invest-140-million-euros-in-wind-power-dunya-says.html
Eczacibasi Holding AS (0111222D) , a Turkish
company with interest in pharmaceuticals and building materials,
plans to spend 140 million euros ($184 million) on a wind power
plant in the country’s northwest,  Dunya newspaper reported ,
citing Chief Executive Officer Erdal Karamercan.  Eczacibasi will join an existing project in Kocaeli
province, and construction will start within a year, Karamercan
said, according to Dunya. The plant will have 110 megawatts of
capacity, he said.  Eczacibasi bought a 50 percent stake in Turkish power
producer Erguvan Enerji Elektrik Uretim AS, the country’s
antitrust body said in February. 